{"lemma":"بُدِّ","slug":"بُدِّ","root":"ب.د.د","root_slug":"ب-د-د","root_link":"/words/roots/ب-د-د","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":false},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":2,"pos_tags":["noun","verb"],"has_etymology":true,"sense_count":7},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n1920","n1929","n1930","n2043"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%A8%D9%8F%D8%AF%D9%90%D9%91"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"noun","gloss":"escape, means of avoiding something","examples":[{"text":"لَا بُدَّ مِن كَذَا","english":"there is no avoiding such a thing, such a thing is inevitable"}]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"flight"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"separation"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"part, portion"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"equivalent, substitute"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"idol"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to disperse, distribute, spread"}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"Noun sense 6 is a semantic loan from Classical Persian بُت (but)."},"ipa":null,"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n1920","headword_ar":"بَدَّ","root":"bd","body":[{"kind":"text","text":", aor."},{"kind":"text","text":", inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bad~N","text_ar":"بَدٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":": see 2. ―         -b2-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bad~a rijolayohi","text_ar":"بَدَّ رِجْلَيْهِ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He parted his legs,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"straddled,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, M, K,) in the stocks, or otherwise. (M.) ―         -b3-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bad~ahu","text_ar":"بَدَّهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (M, K,) aor. and inf. n. as above, (M,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He removed with it, withdrew with it, drew away with it,"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"drew it away,"},{"kind":"text","text":"from its place,] (M, K,) namely, a thing. (M.) ―         -b4-"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He made him"},{"kind":"text","text":"(namely, his companion, M)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"to retire,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"withdraw, far away;"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"to refrain, forbear,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"abstain;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, K;)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eani Al$~aYo'i","text_ar":"عَنِ الشَّىْءِ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"from the thing."},{"kind":"text","text":"(M.) ―         -b5-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^anaA A^abud~u bika Eano *`lika AlA^amori","text_ar":"اَنَا اَبُدُّ بِكَ عَنْ ذٰلِكَ الاَمْرِ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"I will defend thee from that thing,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"event, by repelling it,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"averting it, from thee."},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, L.) ―         -b6-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bud~a Eano dabari Ald~aAb~api","text_ar":"بُدَّ عَنْ دَبَرِ الدَّابَّةِ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"It"},{"kind":"text","text":"(a felt cloth)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"was cut,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"slit, so as to be clear of the galls,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"sores, on the back of the beast."},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, TA.)       -A2-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bad~a","text_ar":"بَدَّ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (M,) second pers."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"badidota","text_ar":"بَدِدْتَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, K,) aor."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"yabad~u","text_ar":"يَبَدُّ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (M,) inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"badadN","text_ar":"بَدَدٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (T, S, M, K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He"},{"kind":"text","text":"(a man)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"was,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"became,"},{"kind":"page_break","n":161},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"wide between the thighs,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(ISk, T, S, M, K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"by reason of abundance of flesh:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(ISk, S, M:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"or wide between the arms;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"having the arms far from the sides:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"wide between the shoulder-joints:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"large in make, having one part far from another."},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, K.) ―         -b2-  Also"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He"},{"kind":"text","text":"(a quadruped, ISk, T, S, or a horse, M)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"had his fore legs far apart:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(ISk, T, S, M:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he"},{"kind":"text","text":"(a horse)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"had his fore legs far from his sides:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Lth, T:) and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he"},{"kind":"text","text":"(a camel)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"had his elbows far from his sides."},{"kind":"text","text":"(T.)       -A3-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bad~a qatabahu","text_ar":"بَدَّ قَتَبَهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", aor."},{"kind":"text","text":","},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He furnished his camel's saddle with what are called"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bidaAdaAni","text_ar":"بِدَادَانِ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"badiydaAni","text_ar":"بَدِيدَانِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S.) [See"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bidaAdN","text_ar":"بِدَادٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"}],"source_refs":["S","M","K","T","ISk","Lth"]},{"entry_id":"n1929","headword_ar":"بُدٌ","root":"bd","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"as signifying"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A separating oneself,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"an artifice whereby one may avoid"},{"kind":"text","text":"a thing or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"escape"},{"kind":"text","text":"from it, (MF,) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"an avoiding"},{"kind":"text","text":"a thing, (Msb,) is not used but in negative phrases, (Msb, MF,) except by post-classical writers. (MF.) You say,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"laA bud~a mino ka*aA","text_ar":"لَا بُدَّ مِنْ كَذَا"},{"kind":"text","text":"(T, S, M, &c.)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"There is no separating oneself from such a thing:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(AA, T, S, A, K:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"there is no artifice whereby one may avoid it,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"escape from it:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, K:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"there is no avoiding it:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"it is absolutely necessary: it is not possible to separate oneself from it, nor is there anything that can serve in its stead."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maA laka minohu bud~N","text_ar":"مَا لَكَ مِنْهُ بُدٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Thou hast not any means,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"way, of separating thyself from it,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"avoiding it"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (M, L.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"layosa lih`*aA AlA^amori","text_ar":"لَيْسَ لِهٰذَا الاَمْرِ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bud~N","text_ar":"بُدٌّ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"There is no artifice for this affair."},{"kind":"text","text":"(T.) [It is also said, with reference to the first of these phrases, that]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bud~N","text_ar":"بُدٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"signifies"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Amplitude;"},{"kind":"text","text":"from"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^abad~u","text_ar":"اَبَدُّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"meaning “ wide between the legs. ” (Ham p. 348.)       -A2-  Also, (M, K,) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bid~N","text_ar":"بِدٌّ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bidaAdN","text_ar":"بِدَادٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"(IAar, T, M, K) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"budaAdN","text_ar":"بُدَادٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (K, TA,) or ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"badaAdN","text_ar":"بَدَادٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (CK,) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bud~apN","text_ar":"بُدَّةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (IAar, T, M, K,) or ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bid~apN","text_ar":"بِدَّةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, A, IAth, and mentioned also in a copy of the K,) but J has been charged with error in writing it thus, (K,) by Sgh, (TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A lot, share, portion,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"set portion;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(T, S, M, A, IAth, K;) of anything: (M, K:) [or] the last signifies"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a piece,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"portion, separated, disunited,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"dispersed:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Ham p. 823:) the pl. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bidaAdN","text_ar":"بِدَادٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bududN","text_ar":"بُدُدٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; and of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"budadN bud~apN","text_ar":"بُدَدٌ بُدَّةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (IAar, T, M;) and of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bidadN bid~apN","text_ar":"بِدَدٌ بِدَّةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (IAth, and Ham p. 823.) ―         -b2-  Also the first,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A substitute; a thing given,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"received,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"put,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"done, instead of, in the place of,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in exchange for, another thing; a compensation;"},{"kind":"text","text":"syn."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EiwaDN","text_ar":"عِوَضٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (S, L, TA:) it is said to have this signification. (S.) [In the copies of the K,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlbaEuwDu","text_ar":"البَعُوضُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is put in the place of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlEiwaDu","text_ar":"العِوَضُ"},{"kind":"text","text":": but this is said in the TA to be a mistake.]       -A3-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bud~N","text_ar":"بُدٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is also an arabicized word, from"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"buto","text_ar":"بُتْ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (T, S, M, K, [in a copy of the M,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"but~","text_ar":"بُتّ"},{"kind":"text","text":",]) which is Persian; (T, S;) meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"An idol;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(IDrd, S, M, K;) pl."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"badadapN","text_ar":"بَدَدَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, K) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^abodaAdN","text_ar":"اَبْدَادٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (K:) and (or accord. to some,"},{"kind":"page_break","n":162},{"kind":"text","text":"TA) the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"house of an idol:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a house in which are idols and images"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"pictures."},{"kind":"text","text":"(M.)"}],"source_refs":["MF","Msb","AA","T","S","A","K","M","IAar","TA","CK","L"]},{"entry_id":"n1930","headword_ar":"بِدٌّ","root":"bd","body":[{"kind":"text","text":": see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bud~N","text_ar":"بُدٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":". ―         -b2-  Also, and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"badiydN","text_ar":"بَدِيدٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"(T, K) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"badiydapN","text_ar":"بَدِيدَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A like; a fellow; an equal."},{"kind":"text","text":"(T, K.) You say,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"huwa bid~uhu","text_ar":"هُوَ بِدُّهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"badiyduhu","text_ar":"بَدِيدُهُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"it, is the like, &c., of him,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"it."},{"kind":"text","text":"(T.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"huma bid~aAni","text_ar":"هُمَ بِدَّانِ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"They two are likes,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"fellows,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"equals."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fatukal~imaniY","text_ar":"فَتُكَلِّمَنِى"},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maA A^anota liY bibadiydK","text_ar":"مَا اَنْتَ لِى بِبَدِيدٍ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Thou art not my like,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"fellow,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"equal, that thou shouldst speak to me."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.)"}],"source_refs":["T","K"]},{"entry_id":"n2043","headword_ar":"بَدٍ","root":"bdw","body":[{"kind":"text","text":": see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"badowN","text_ar":"بَدْوٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", in two places."}],"source_refs":[]}]},"classical_definitions":null}